results.name: Triangle read by rows: T(n,k) is the number of graphs with n vertices with edge connectivity k.
comment: This is spanning edge-connectivity. The spanning edge-connectivity of a graph is the minimum number of edges that must be removed (without removing incident vertices) to obtain a graph that is disconnected or covers fewer vertices. The non-spanning edge-connectivity of a graph (A327236) is the minimum number of edges that must be removed to obtain a graph whose edge-set is disconnected or empty. Compare to vertex-connectivity (A259862). - _Gus Wiseman_, Sep 03 2019
